&DYearby=All%20Seasons |archivedate=4 December 2013  }}</ref>\n*Fourth highest number of games as captain of the [[England national football team]]: 59.<ref name=\"Beckham stands down\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://englandfootballonline.com/TeamCapt/CaptBio/CaptBeckhamDRJ.html|title=David Beckham - Captain Statistics|access-date=5 November 2019|date=1 May 2011}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Association football|English football}}\n*[[Beckham rule]]\n*[[List of footballers with more than 100 international caps]]\n*[[List of professional sports team owners]]\n{{Clear}}\n\n==References==\n\n===Books===\n* {{Cite book |last1=Beckham |first1=David |title=David Beckham: My Side |publisher=HarperCollinsWillow |year=2002 |isbn=978-0-00-715732-7 }}\n* {{Cite book |last1=Beckham |first1=David |last2=Freeman |first2=Dean |title=Beckham: My World |publisher=Hodder & Stoughton |year=2001 |isbn=978-0-340-79270-4 |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/beckhammyworld0000beck_i7u3 }}\n* {{Cite book |last1=Beckham |first1=David |last2=Watt |first2=Tom |title=Beckham: Both Feet on the Ground |publisher=HarperCollins |year=2003 |isbn=978-0-06-057093-4 |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/beckhambothfeeto00beck }}\n* {{Cite book |last=Crick |first=Michael |title=The Boss \u2013 The Many Sides of Alex Ferguson |publisher=Pocket Books |year=2003 |isbn=978-0-7434-2991-7 |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/bossmanysidesofa0000cric }}\n* {{Cite book |last1=Ferguson |first1=Alex |last2=McIlvanney |first2=Hugh |title=Managing My Life \u2013 My Autobiography |publisher=Hodder & Stoughton |year=1999 |isbn=978-0-340-72855-0 |url=https://archive.org/details/managingmylife00alex }}\n* {{Cite book |last=Wahl |first=Grant |title=The Beckham Experiment: How the World's Most Famous Athlete Tried to Conquer America |publisher=Crown |year=2009 |isbn=978-0-307-40859-4 }}\n\n===Internet===\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*{{cite magazine|